 IMPORTANT: The result is only valid if the success flag is true. When using this function, make sure the chain
 you're using it on supports the precompiled contract for modular exponentiation at address 0x05 as specified in
 https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-198[EIP-198]. Otherwise, the underlying function will succeed given the lack
 of a revert, but the result may be incorrectly interpreted as 0.

@dev Wrappers over Solidity's uintXX/intXX/bool casting operators with added overflow
 checks.
 Downcasting from uint256/int256 in Solidity does not revert on overflow. This can
 easily result in undesired exploitation or bugs, since developers usually
 assume that overflows raise errors. `SafeCast` restores this intuition by
 reverting the transaction when such an operation overflows.
 Using this library instead of the unchecked operations eliminates an entire
 class of bugs, so it's recommended to use it always.

devdoc.details: Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to specific functions. The initial owner is set to the address provided by the deployer. This can later be changed with {transferOwnership}. This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier `onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to the owner.

OwnableInvalidOwner(address).details: The owner is not a valid owner account. (eg. `address(0)`)

OwnableUnauthorizedAccount(address).details: The caller account is not authorized to perform an operation.

constructor.details: Initializes the contract setting the address provided by the deployer as the initial owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

Approval(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `owner` enables `approved` to manage the `tokenId` token.

ApprovalForAll(address,address,bool).details: Emitted when `owner` enables or disables (`approved`) `operator` to manage all of its assets.

Transfer(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `tokenId` token is transferred from `from` to `to`.

approve(address,uint256).details: Gives permission to `to` to transfer `tokenId` token to another account. The approval is cleared when the token is transferred. Only a single account can be approved at a time, so approving the zero address clears previous approvals. Requirements: - The caller must own the token or be an approved operator. - `tokenId` must exist. Emits an {Approval} event.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the number of tokens in ``owner``'s account.

constructor.details: Initializes the contract by setting a `name` and a `symbol` to the token collection.

getApproved(uint256).details: Returns the account approved for `tokenId` token. Requirements: - `tokenId` must exist.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Returns if the `operator` is allowed to manage all of the assets of `owner`. See {setApprovalForAll}

ownerOf(uint256).details: Returns the owner of the `tokenId` token. Requirements: - `tokenId` must exist.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers `tokenId` token from `from` to `to`, checking first that contract recipients are aware of the ERC-721 protocol to prevent tokens from being forever locked. Requirements: - `from` cannot be the zero address. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - `tokenId` token must exist and be owned by `from`. - If the caller is not `from`, it must have been allowed to move this token by either {approve} or   {setApprovalForAll}. - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}, which is called upon   a safe transfer. devdoc.details: Contract module which allows children to implement an emergency stop mechanism that can be triggered by an authorized account. This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifiers `whenNotPaused` and `whenPaused`, which can be applied to the functions of your contract. Note that they will not be pausable by simply including this module, only once the modifiers are put in place.

ExpectedPause().details: The operation failed because the contract is not paused.

Paused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is triggered by `account`.

Unpaused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is lifted by `account`.

devdoc.details: Contract module that helps prevent reentrant calls to a function. Inheriting from `ReentrancyGuard` will make the {nonReentrant} modifier available, which can be applied to functions to make sure there are no nested (reentrant) calls to them. Note that because there is a single `nonReentrant` guard, functions marked as `nonReentrant` may not call one another. This can be worked around by making those functions `private`, and then adding `external` `nonReentrant` entry points to them. TIP: If EIP-1153 (transient storage) is available on the chain you're deploying at, consider using {ReentrancyGuardTransient} instead. TIP: If you would like to learn more about reentrancy and alternative ways to protect against it, check out our blog post https://blog.openzeppelin.com/reentrancy-after-istanbul/[Reentrancy After Istanbul].

devdoc.details: Implementation of the {IERC165} interface. Contracts that want to implement ERC-165 should inherit from this contract and override {supportsInterface} to check for the additional interface id that will be supported. For example: ```solidity function supportsInterface(bytes4 interfaceId) public view virtual override returns (bool) {     return interfaceId == type(MyInterface).interfaceId || super.supportsInterface(interfaceId); } ```

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[ERC section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

devdoc.details: Interface of the ERC-165 standard, as defined in the https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165[ERC]. Implementers can declare support of contract interfaces, which can then be queried by others ({ERC165Checker}). For an implementation, see {ERC165}.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. devdoc.details: Wrappers over Solidity's uintXX/intXX/bool casting operators with added overflow checks. Downcasting from uint256/int256 in Solidity does not revert on overflow. This can easily result in undesired exploitation or bugs, since developers usually assume that overflows raise errors. `SafeCast` restores this intuition by reverting the transaction when such an operation overflows. Using this library instead of the unchecked operations eliminates an entire class of bugs, so it's recommended to use it always.

devdoc.details: ERC-721 contract for event tickets with seat mapping Each ticket represents one seat (1-N occupancy)

ERC721IncorrectOwner(address,uint256,add.details: Indicates an error related to the ownership over a particular token. Used in transfers.

params.owner: Address of the current owner of a token.
params.sender: Address whose tokens are being transferred.

ERC721InsufficientApproval(address,uint2.details: Indicates a failure with the `operator`’s approval. Used in transfers.

params.operator: Address that may be allowed to operate on tokens without being their owner.

ERC721InvalidApprover(address).details: Indicates a failure with the `approver` of a token to be approved. Used in approvals.

ERC721InvalidOperator(address).details: Indicates a failure with the `operator` to be approved. Used in approvals.

params.operator: Address that may be allowed to operate on tokens without being their owner.

ERC721InvalidOwner(address).details: Indicates that an address can't be an owner. For example, `address(0)` is a forbidden owner in ERC-20. Used in balance queries.

params.owner: Address of the current owner of a token.

ERC721InvalidReceiver(address).details: Indicates a failure with the token `receiver`. Used in transfers.

params.receiver: Address to which tokens are being transferred.

ERC721InvalidSender(address).details: Indicates a failure with the token `sender`. Used in transfers.

params.sender: Address whose tokens are being transferred.

ERC721NonexistentToken(uint256).details: Indicates a `tokenId` whose `owner` is the zero address.

OwnableInvalidOwner(address).details: The owner is not a valid owner account. (eg. `address(0)`)

OwnableUnauthorizedAccount(address).details: The caller account is not authorized to perform an operation.

Approval(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `owner` enables `approved` to manage the `tokenId` token.

ApprovalForAll(address,address,bool).details: Emitted when `owner` enables or disables (`approved`) `operator` to manage all of its assets.

Transfer(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `tokenId` token is transferred from `from` to `to`.

approve(address,uint256).details: Gives permission to `to` to transfer `tokenId` token to another account. The approval is cleared when the token is transferred. Only a single account can be approved at a time, so approving the zero address clears previous approvals. Requirements: - The caller must own the token or be an approved operator. - `tokenId` must exist. Emits an {Approval} event.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the number of tokens in ``owner``'s account.

buyTicket(string,string).details: Buy a ticket directly from the event

params.tierName: Name of the tier to purchase

returns._0: tierNames Array of all tier names

getApproved(uint256).details: Returns the account approved for `tokenId` token. Requirements: - `tokenId` must exist.

getSeatNumber(uint256).details: Get seat number by token ID

getTicket(uint256).details: Get ticket information by token ID

returns._0: totalMinted Total number of tickets minted
userTicketIds Array of token IDs owned by the user

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Returns if the `operator` is allowed to manage all of the assets of `owner`. See {setApprovalForAll}

returns._0: occupied True if seat is occupied

mintTicket(address,uint256,string,string.details: Mint a ticket for a specific seat and tier (organizer only)

params.to: Address to mint the ticket to

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

ownerOf(uint256).details: Returns the owner of the `tokenId` token. Requirements: - `tokenId` must exist.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers `tokenId` token from `from` to `to`, checking first that contract recipients are aware of the ERC-721 protocol to prevent tokens from being forever locked. Requirements: - `from` cannot be the zero address. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - `tokenId` token must exist and be owned by `from`. - If the caller is not `from`, it must have been allowed to move this token by either {approve} or   {setApprovalForAll}. - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}, which is called upon   a safe transfer. Emits a {Transfer} event.

Safely transfers `tokenId` token from `from` to `to`. Requirements: - `from` cannot be the zero address. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - `tokenId` token must exist and be owned by `from`. - If the caller is not `from`, it must be approved to move this token by either {approve} or {setApprovalForAll}. - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}, which is called upon   a safe transfer. Emits a {Transfer} event.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Approve or remove `operator` as an operator for the caller. Operators can call {transferFrom} or {safeTransferFrom} for any token owned by the caller. Requirements: - The `operator` cannot be the address zero. Emits an {ApprovalForAll} event.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[ERC section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers `tokenId` token from `from` to `to`. WARNING: Note that the caller is responsible to confirm that the recipient is capable of receiving ERC-721 or else they may be permanently lost. Usage of {safeTransferFrom} prevents loss, though the caller must understand this adds an external call which potentially creates a reentrancy vulnerability. Requirements: - `from` cannot be the zero address. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - `tokenId` token must be owned by `from`. - If the caller is not `from`, it must be approved to move this token by either {approve} or {setApprovalForAll}. Emits a {Transfer} event.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

^0.8.20;\r\n\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol\";\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/access/Ownable.sol\";\r\n\r\n/**\r\n * @title EventTicket\r\n * @dev ERC-721 contract for event tickets with seat mapping\r\n * Each ticket represents one seat (1-N occupancy)\r\n */\r\ncontract EventTicket is ERC721, Ownable {\r\n    \r\n    // Events\r\n    event TicketMinted(\r\n        uint256 indexed tokenId,\r\n        address indexed to,\r\n        uint256 seatNumber,\r\n        string tier,\r\n        string metadataURI\r\n    );\r\n    \r\n    event TicketPurchased(\r\n        address indexed buyer,\r\n        uint256 indexed tokenId,\r\n        string tier,\r\n        uint256 price,\r\n        uint256 seatNumber\r\n    );\r\n    \r\n    event TierAdded(\r\n        string tierName,\r\n        uint256 tierPrice,\r\n        uint256 tierQuantity\r\n    );\r\n    \r\n    // State variables\r\n    string public eventName;\r\n    string public eventDescription;\r\n    uint256 public maxOccupancy;\r\n    uint256 public eventDate;\r\n    address public eventOrganizer;\r\n    \r\n    uint256 private _tokenIdCounter;\r\n    \r\n    // Mappings for metadata\r\n    mapping(uint256 => string) private _tokenURIs;\r\n    \r\n    // Structs\r\n    struct Tier {\r\n        string name;\r\n        uint256 price;\r\n        uint256 quantity;\r\n        uint256 minted;\r\n        bool exists;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    struct Ticket {\r\n        uint256 tokenId;\r\n        uint256 seatNumber;\r\n        string tier;\r\n        string metadataURI;\r\n        address owner;\r\n        bool exists;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    // Mappings\r\n    mapping(string => Tier) public tiers;\r\n    mapping(uint256 => Ticket) public tickets;\r\n    mapping(uint256 => uint256) public tokenIdToSeatNumber;\r\n    mapping(uint256 => string) public tokenIdToTier;\r\n    mapping(uint256 => bool) public seatOccupied;\r\n    mapping(address => uint256[]) public userTickets;\r\n    \r\n    string[] public tierNames;\r\n    \r\n    // Modifiers\r\n    modifier onlyEventOrganizer() {\r\n        require(msg.sender == eventOrganizer, \"Only event organizer can call this function\");\r\n        _;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n\r\n    \r\n    modifier validSeatNumber(uint256 seatNumber) {\r\n        require(seatNumber > 0 && seatNumber <= maxOccupancy, \"Invalid seat number\");\r\n        require(!seatOccupied[seatNumber], \"Seat already occupied\");\r\n        _;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    modifier validTier(string memory tierName) {\r\n        require(tiers[tierName].exists, \"Tier does not exist\");\r\n        require(tiers[tierName].minted < tiers[tierName].quantity, \"Tier sold out\");\r\n        _;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    modifier validPurchase(string memory tierName) {\r\n        require(tiers[tierName].exists, \"Tier does not exist\");\r\n        require(tiers[tierName].minted < tiers[tierName].quantity, \"Tier sold out\");\r\n        require(msg.value >= tiers[tierName].price, \"Insufficient payment\");\r\n        _;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    constructor(\r\n        string memory _eventName,\r\n        string memory _eventDescription,\r\n        uint256 _maxOccupancy,\r\n        uint256[] memory _tierPrices,\r\n        string[] memory _tierNames,\r\n        uint256[] memory _tierQuantities,\r\n        uint256 _eventDate,\r\n        address _eventOrganizer\r\n    ) ERC721(_eventName, \"EVENT\") Ownable(_eventOrganizer) {\r\n        eventName = _eventName;\r\n        eventDescription = _eventDescription;\r\n        maxOccupancy = _maxOccupancy;\r\n        eventDate = _eventDate;\r\n        eventOrganizer = _eventOrganizer;\r\n        \r\n        require(_tierNames.length == _tierQuantities.length, \"Tier arrays length mismatch\");\r\n        \r\n        // Initialize tiers with quantities\r\n        for (uint256 i = 0; i < _tierNames.length; i++) {\r\n            require(bytes(_tierNames[i]).length > 0, \"Tier name cannot be empty\");\r\n            require(_tierPrices[i] > 0, \"Tier price must be greater than 0\");\r\n            require(_tierQuantities[i] > 0, \"Tier quantity must be greater than 0\");\r\n            \r\n            tiers[_tierNames[i]] = Tier({\r\n                name: _tierNames[i],\r\n                price: _tierPrices[i],\r\n                quantity: _tierQuantities[i], // Set quantity directly\r\n                minted: 0,\r\n                exists: true\r\n            });\r\n            \r\n            tierNames.push(_tierNames[i]);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Buy a ticket directly from the event\r\n     * @param tierName Name of the tier to purchase\r\n     * @param metadataURI IPFS URI for ticket metadata\r\n     * @return tokenId The minted token ID\r\n     */\r\n    function buyTicket(\r\n        string memory tierName,\r\n        string memory metadataURI\r\n    ) external payable validPurchase(tierName) returns (uint256) {\r\n        // Find next available seat\r\n        uint256 seatNumber = _findNextAvailableSeat();\r\n        require(seatNumber > 0, \"No available seats\");\r\n        \r\n        _tokenIdCounter++;\r\n        uint256 tokenId = _tokenIdCounter;\r\n        \r\n        // Mark seat as occupied\r\n        seatOccupied[seatNumber] = true;\r\n        \r\n        // Create ticket\r\n        tickets[tokenId] = Ticket({\r\n            tokenId: tokenId,\r\n            seatNumber: seatNumber,\r\n            tier: tierName,\r\n            metadataURI: metadataURI,\r\n            owner: msg.sender,\r\n            exists: true\r\n        });\r\n        \r\n        // Update mappings\r\n        tokenIdToSeatNumber[tokenId] = seatNumber;\r\n        tokenIdToTier[tokenId] = tierName;\r\n        userTickets[msg.sender].push(tokenId);\r\n        \r\n        // Set token URI\r\n        _setTokenURI(tokenId, metadataURI);\r\n        \r\n        // Update tier minted count\r\n        tiers[tierName].minted++;\r\n        \r\n        // Mint NFT\r\n        _safeMint(msg.sender, tokenId);\r\n        \r\n        // Transfer payment to event organizer\r\n        payable(eventOrganizer).transfer(msg.value);\r\n        \r\n        emit TicketPurchased(msg.sender, tokenId, tierName, msg.value, seatNumber);\r\n        emit TicketMinted(tokenId, msg.sender, seatNumber, tierName, metadataURI);\r\n        \r\n        return tokenId;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Find the next available seat number\r\n     * @return seatNumber The next available seat number, or 0 if none available\r\n     */\r\n    function _findNextAvailableSeat() internal view returns (uint256) {\r\n        for (uint256 i = 1; i <= maxOccupancy; i++) {\r\n            if (!seatOccupied[i]) {\r\n                return i;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        return 0;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Mint a ticket for a specific seat and tier (organizer only)\r\n     * @param to Address to mint the ticket to\r\n     * @param seatNumber Seat number (1-N)\r\n     * @param tierName Name of the tier\r\n     * @param metadataURI IPFS URI for ticket metadata\r\n     * @return tokenId The minted token ID\r\n     */\r\n    function mintTicket(\r\n        address to,\r\n        uint256 seatNumber,\r\n        string memory tierName,\r\n        string memory metadataURI\r\n    ) external onlyEventOrganizer validSeatNumber(seatNumber) validTier(tierName) returns (uint256) {\r\n        require(to != address(0), \"Cannot mint to zero address\");\r\n        \r\n        _tokenIdCounter++;\r\n        uint256 tokenId = _tokenIdCounter;\r\n        \r\n        // Mark seat as occupied\r\n        seatOccupied[seatNumber] = true;\r\n        \r\n        // Create ticket\r\n        tickets[tokenId] = Ticket({\r\n            tokenId: tokenId,\r\n            seatNumber: seatNumber,\r\n            tier: tierName,\r\n            metadataURI: metadataURI,\r\n            owner: to,\r\n            exists: true\r\n        });\r\n        \r\n        // Update mappings\r\n        tokenIdToSeatNumber[tokenId] = seatNumber;\r\n        tokenIdToTier[tokenId] = tierName;\r\n        userTickets[to].push(tokenId);\r\n        \r\n        // Set token URI\r\n        _setTokenURI(tokenId, metadataURI);\r\n        \r\n        // Update tier minted count\r\n        tiers[tierName].minted++;\r\n        \r\n        // Mint NFT\r\n        _safeMint(to, tokenId);\r\n        \r\n        emit TicketMinted(tokenId, to, seatNumber, tierName, metadataURI);\r\n        \r\n        return tokenId;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get ticket information by token ID\r\n     * @param tokenId The token ID\r\n     * @return ticket The ticket information\r\n     */\r\n    function getTicket(uint256 tokenId) external view returns (Ticket memory) {\r\n        require(ownerOf(tokenId) != address(0), \"Token does not exist\");\r\n        return tickets[tokenId];\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get seat number by token ID\r\n     * @param tokenId The token ID\r\n     * @return seatNumber The seat number\r\n     */\r\n    function getSeatNumber(uint256 tokenId) external view returns (uint256) {\r\n        require(ownerOf(tokenId) != address(0), \"Token does not exist\");\r\n        return tokenIdToSeatNumber[tokenId];\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get tier by token ID\r\n     * @param tokenId The token ID\r\n     * @return tier The tier name\r\n     */\r\n    function getTicketTier(uint256 tokenId) external view returns (string memory) {\r\n        require(ownerOf(tokenId) != address(0), \"Token does not exist\");\r\n        return tokenIdToTier[tokenId];\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get user's tickets\r\n     * @param user Address of the user\r\n     * @return userTicketIds Array of token IDs owned by the user\r\n     */\r\n    function getUserTickets(address user) external view returns (uint256[] memory) {\r\n        return userTickets[user];\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get tier information\r\n     * @param tierName Name of the tier\r\n     * @return tier The tier information\r\n     */\r\n    function getTier(string memory tierName) external view returns (Tier memory) {\r\n        require(tiers[tierName].exists, \"Tier does not exist\");\r\n        return tiers[tierName];\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get all tier names\r\n     * @return tierNames Array of all tier names\r\n     */\r\n    function getAllTierNames() external view returns (string[] memory) {\r\n        return tierNames;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Check if seat is occupied\r\n     * @param seatNumber The seat number to check\r\n     * @return occupied True if seat is occupied\r\n     */\r\n    function isSeatOccupied(uint256 seatNumber) external view returns (bool) {\r\n        return seatOccupied[seatNumber];\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get total tickets minted\r\n     * @return totalMinted Total number of tickets minted\r\n     */\r\n    function getTotalMinted() external view returns (uint256) {\r\n        return _tokenIdCounter;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get available seats count\r\n     * @return availableSeats Number of available seats\r\n     */\r\n    function getAvailableSeats() external view returns (uint256) {\r\n        return maxOccupancy - _tokenIdCounter;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Set token URI\r\n     * @param tokenId The token ID\r\n     * @param uri The URI to set\r\n     */\r\n    function _setTokenURI(uint256 tokenId, string memory uri) internal {\r\n        _tokenURIs[tokenId] = uri;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @dev Get token URI\r\n     * @param tokenId The token ID\r\n     * @return The URI for the token\r\n     */\r\n    function tokenURI(uint256 tokenId) public view override returns (string memory) {\r\n        require(ownerOf(tokenId) != address(0), \"Token does not exist\");\r\n        string memory uri = _tokenURIs[tokenId];\r\n        if (bytes(uri).length > 0) {\r\n            return uri;\r\n        }\r\n        return super.tokenURI(tokenId);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n","keccak256":"0x3549224497f91bd3217e018cfae4fc8738dc2244fa28e9a655ca65581e6a804d","license":"MIT"}},"version":1}
